
Object cloning : creating a new object using the exisiting object and its Data in the
                 DATA MEMBERS is called object cloning
                 
- To clone an object the class must override the clone() of the Object class  

- The class should also implements the Cloneable interface

- Cloneable is a marker interface which is an empty interface without any methods or variables.

- A class implements the Cloneable interface to
  indicate to the clone() method that it is legal for that method to make a
  DATA MEMBER-for-DATA MEMBER copy of Objects of that class.           
                 